      .col-md-9
        p 
        p I partnered up with an NYC Cleaning Service company wanting to automate their services. They had a non-functioning MVP and a clear goal before reaching out. 
      
        p  The application that they were using previously failed to adapt to the increasingly complex demands of new features to support a growing cleaning service company. 
        p The company used another a third party software service that even though offered data about bookings and quotes, was missing the customer features and a way to keep everything organized.
